PROCEDURE: FCA Regulatory Compliance Review
TRIGGER: Monthly regulatory compliance assessment or audit trigger event
TOOLS: compliance_db, audit_trail_system, regulatory_api, risk_calculator, reporting_engine

1. Initialize comprehensive compliance review process for current reporting period
2. Query compliance_db to retrieve all transaction records for the review period
3. Calculate total transaction volumes and values across all customer segments
4. Check if any transaction volumes exceed FCA reporting thresholds for large exposures
   - YES: Flag for detailed Large Exposure reporting and proceed to step 5
   - NO: Proceed to step 7
5. Generate Large Exposure report with detailed counterparty analysis
6. Submit Large Exposure data to FCA via regulatory_api within required timeframe
7. Review all customer onboarding activities completed during the period
8. Verify that KYC documentation meets current FCA standards for all new customers
9. Check if any customer onboarding files are missing required documentation
   - YES: Generate deficiency report and escalate to compliance_officer
   - NO: Proceed to step 10
10. Analyze all AML alerts and investigations conducted during the review period
11. Calculate the percentage of AML alerts that resulted in Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)
12. Check if SAR filing rate is within expected industry benchmarks (2-5% of alerts)
    - YES: Proceed to step 13
    - NO: Investigate potential under-reporting and escalate to aml_compliance_head
13. Review all customer complaints and their resolution outcomes
14. Verify that complaint resolution times meet FCA requirements (15 business days standard)
15. Check if any complaints were escalated to Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS)
    - YES: Review FOS cases for potential systemic issues and proceed to step 16
    - NO: Proceed to step 17
16. Analyze FOS escalation patterns to identify root cause compliance gaps
17. Query audit_trail_system for all privileged access events and system changes
18. Verify that all system modifications were properly authorized and documented
19. Check if any unauthorized access attempts or security breaches occurred
    - YES: Escalate to information_security_team and regulatory_affairs
    - NO: Proceed to step 20
20. Calculate firm-wide risk metrics using risk_calculator for capital adequacy assessment
21. Verify that capital ratios meet FCA minimum requirements plus internal buffers
22. Check if stress test scenarios indicate potential capital adequacy concerns
    - YES: Generate early warning report for senior_management and FCA
    - NO: Proceed to step 23
23. Compile all regulatory metrics into comprehensive compliance dashboard
24. Generate automated regulatory returns using reporting_engine for FCA submission
25. Schedule management attestation review for all regulatory submissions
26. Archive all compliance evidence and audit trails for regulatory retention requirements and end